    "text": [
        "In the modern era, technology is advanced and changed our social lives. Moreover, digital media is best way to talk with any person and share data across the globe. But sharing of the information can also disturb the privacy of individual. This essay will discuss the both sides of arguments and then submits a plausible opinion.",
        "To begin with, many applications are developed such as  Whats app, IMO and many more which assists to have  a link with family and friends who are miles away. Furthermore, Google map gives the destination to reach in less time and convenient way. For example, Zoom application aids professional to attend meeting and conference online in different modes (individuals or in groups). In addition to this, job-seekers can easily find jobs and get selected through video and telephonic interviews. Hence, it also helps to increase the knowledge related to any topic.",
        "On another hand, people update all details on Facebook which assists to hacker or criminals to find the person without any difficulty. By sharing these details, breaches their privacy. For instance, on the installation of any software or application, permission is to be accessed. Firstly, if given the access it means we are providing full rights to control the device. Secondly, fraudster making money by sending links on mobiles or emails. Many inappropriate contents are available which has devastating effects on adolescents. Thus, many humans have bad experience and lose confidence from sites.",
        "To conclude, social media is essential part of life and connect everyone throughout the world. In my opinion, life is incomplete without these social platforms. In future more people will use these websites for their convenience."
